works.description: After the FlyNano single-seat fun flyer, we have AutoGyro’s Cavalon gyrocopter from the Aero Friedrichshafen air show held in Germany (April 13-16). The side-by-side, fully enclosed Cavalon gyrocopter presents its pilot and passenger with an unrivaled dimension and comfort. Invented by the Spanish engineer Juan de la Cierva in 1923, a gyrocopter is quite stable at low speeds, and it doesn’t need much space for the take-off and landing. The AutoGyro’s Cavalon gyrocopter has already been certified in Germany and France, with other countries to follow.
